Company Description                    




                        BlueFocus Communication Group Co., Ltd. was founded in2002, main business and services include: public relationsstrategy consulting, public communication, media relations,crisis management, investor relations, corporate imagemanagement, and event management. Business areas coveringIT, telecommunications, finance, medical, FMCG, consumerdurables (cars, household appliances), government andnon-profit organization.The clients are mostly the leading companies in theindustries, in which 28 customers in Fortune 500enterprises. At present, key clients include Lenovo, Cisco,Canon, Tencent, Sony, Sony Ericsson, AMD, Microsoft,Samsung, Motorola, Nokia, Guangzhou Toyota, Chrysler, BMW,Wrigley chewing gum, Mead Johnson, Bosch, Siemens, Ya PoetryLauder Glaxo SmithKline, Pfizer, DuPont, Carrefour, MorganStanley, etc.The company was selected as No.75 in "250 Global PublicRelation Companies" by The Holmes Report in 2007; as thebest public relations firm in "Greater China Consultancyof the Year" by The Holmes Report in 2008; and was namedForbes "the potential of China Top 250 Enterprises" ofChinese version published in 2009.                    


